==English==

===Etymology===
{{confix|en|sclero|enchyma}} (hard, scalous tissue)

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˌsklɪəɹəŋˈkaɪmə/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|s|sclerenchymata}}

# {{lb|en|botany}} A mechanical [[ground tissue]], impermeable to water which consists of [[cell]]s having narrow [[lumen]] and thick, mineralized walls of [[lignin]]; present in stems, vascular bundles(of [[monocot|monocots]]), seed coverings, and in vein and tips of leaves.
# {{lb|en|zoology}} The hard [[calcareous]] [[deposit]] in the [[tissue]]s of the [[stony coral]]s ([[Anthozoa]]).<!--Webster 1913-->

